feature.summary: The Prioritization of VoLTE in Access Barring feature allows for the prioritization

parameters.name: EUtranCellFDD.acBarringPresence  EUtranCellTDD.acBarringPresence
parameters.description: The Prioritization of VoLTE in Access Barring indicators (when                                 enabled by operator) are only broadcast when access class barring is                                 enabled and broadcast.

parameters.name: EUtranCellFDD.ssacBarringForMMTELVideo  EUtranCellTDD.ssacBarringForMMTELVideo
parameters.description: The Prioritization of VoLTE in Access Barring feature is independent                                 of SSAC, but there is some interaction at the UE node. If SSAC is                                 set to be barred for a UE, the IMS layer in the UE stops the                                 connection attempt before it reaches the point where an RRC                                 connection is attempted. In this case, the setting of the Prioritization of VoLTE in Access Barring indication does not matter.
